WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:23.000
Cheedeb presents The True Story of Pocahontas by Kelly Reinhardt.

00:30.000 --> 00:59.000
The Indian Princess Pocahontas was born near Jamestown in 1595.

01:00.000 --> 01:08.000
Captain John Smith wrote many of the events of this story in his books.

01:08.000 --> 01:14.000
Some details were added and other details were forgotten.

01:14.000 --> 01:20.000
But the story you will read in this book really happened.

01:20.000 --> 01:27.000
This is The True Story of Pocahontas.

01:28.000 --> 01:34.000
Chapter 1 The Sailing Ship

01:34.000 --> 01:40.000
May was a beautiful month in the land of the Algonquin Indians.

01:40.000 --> 01:45.000
There were tall trees and colorful flowers everywhere.

01:45.000 --> 01:50.000
The sky and the sea were deep blue.

01:50.000 --> 01:57.000
Pocahontas was the favorite daughter of Chief Pocahontas.

01:57.000 --> 02:00.000
She was an Indian princess.

02:00.000 --> 02:07.000
Chief Pocahontas was a powerful chief of the Algonquin tribe.

02:07.000 --> 02:12.000
Pocahontas was 11 years old.

02:12.000 --> 02:18.000
She was a lovely young girl with black hair and dark eyes.

02:18.000 --> 02:23.000
She wore a buckskin dress and moccasins.

02:23.000 --> 02:27.000
She had a feather in her hair.

02:27.000 --> 02:31.000
Pocahontas was always happy.

02:31.000 --> 02:36.000
She ran in the forest and danced in the fields.

02:36.000 --> 02:41.000
She sat on the hill and looked at the blue sea.

02:42.000 --> 02:53.000
On May 6, 1607, Pocahontas sat on the hill and she saw something strange in the bay.

02:53.000 --> 02:57.000
It was a big sailing ship.

02:57.000 --> 03:00.000
She was very surprised.

03:00.000 --> 03:04.000
The sailing ship was something new.

03:04.000 --> 03:09.000
It had big white sails and flags.

03:09.000 --> 03:13.000
She looked at it for a long time.

03:13.000 --> 03:15.000
Where did it come from?

03:15.000 --> 03:18.000
Why was it there?

03:18.000 --> 03:22.000
She was very excited.

03:22.000 --> 03:28.000
Pocahontas ran to her village to tell her father and brother the news.

03:28.000 --> 03:30.000
Father, father!

03:30.000 --> 03:34.000
She said, there's a big sailing ship in the bay.

03:34.000 --> 03:39.000
It has white sails and coloured flags.

03:39.000 --> 03:45.000
Her father, Chief Pocahontan, was outside his long house.

03:45.000 --> 03:50.000
He was a tall man with long black hair.

03:50.000 --> 03:55.000
He wore the feathers of an Indian chief on his head.

03:55.000 --> 04:00.000
He listened to the news, but he was not happy.

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
The white men are here.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
Pocahontan said sadly.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.000
This is bad news for our people.

04:07.000 --> 04:12.000
There is no peace with the white men here.

04:12.000 --> 04:16.000
Nantakwas was Pocahontas' brother.

04:16.000 --> 04:19.000
He was 18 years old.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
He was a strong Indian warrior.

04:23.000 --> 04:26.000
He looked at his sister and said,

04:26.000 --> 04:30.000
In the past, the white people killed the Indians.

04:30.000 --> 04:33.000
They want to take our land.

04:33.000 --> 04:38.000
Oh, Nantakwas, let's go to see the white people.

04:38.000 --> 04:41.000
Let's go to see their big ship.

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
Said Pocahontas.

04:44.000 --> 04:50.000
You can go to see them, but don't go near the ship.

04:50.000 --> 04:52.000
Stay far away.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
Be careful.

04:54.000 --> 04:57.000
Said Pocahontan.

04:57.000 --> 05:00.000
Remember Pocahontas.

05:00.000 --> 05:04.000
White men are dangerous.

05:04.000 --> 05:08.000
Nantakwas and Pocahontas went to the river.

05:08.000 --> 05:12.000
There were many canoes near the river.

05:12.000 --> 05:15.000
They got into a small canoe.

05:15.000 --> 05:21.000
Then Nantakwas paddled down the river to the bay.

05:21.000 --> 05:26.000
In the bay, they saw the big sailing ship.

05:26.000 --> 05:30.000
There was a tall white man on the ship.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
He smiled at them.

05:32.000 --> 05:36.000
There were other white men too.

05:36.000 --> 05:41.000
They all looked at the small canoe and at the two Indians.

05:41.000 --> 05:44.000
Pocahontas smiled at the white man.

05:44.000 --> 05:46.000
Let's go to the ship.

05:46.000 --> 05:48.000
She said.

05:48.000 --> 05:49.000
No.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
Said Nantakwas.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.000
It's dangerous.

05:53.000 --> 05:56.000
We don't know who these white men are.

05:56.000 --> 05:59.000
We can look and then go home.

05:59.000 --> 06:02.000
We must obey our father.

06:02.000 --> 06:05.000
The white man on the ship smiled again.

06:05.000 --> 06:07.000
Look Nantakwas.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.000
Said Pocahontas.

06:09.000 --> 06:13.000
That man has red hair and white skin.

06:13.000 --> 06:16.000
He's smiling at us.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.000
Look at his clothes.

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
They are strange.

06:20.000 --> 06:25.000
Nantakwas turned the canoe and paddled up the river.

06:25.000 --> 06:29.000
When they arrived home, Nantakwas said.

06:29.000 --> 06:32.000
I saw a big sailing ship.

06:32.000 --> 06:35.000
There were many white men on the ship.

06:35.000 --> 06:41.000
Pocahontas talked to his medicine men and tribe advisors.

06:41.000 --> 06:46.000
They all sat inside the long house for a long time.

06:46.000 --> 06:48.000
He said.

06:48.000 --> 06:51.000
White men bring us problems.

06:51.000 --> 06:54.000
They have a strange magic.

06:54.000 --> 06:58.000
They carry thundersticks to kill our people.

06:58.000 --> 07:04.000
They want to take our land, our lakes, our rivers and our forests.

07:04.000 --> 07:10.000
They can stay for a short time, but they cannot stay here forever.

07:10.000 --> 07:14.000
Let's watch them and see what they do.

