10:26.880 --> 10:28.880
Chapter Two.

10:28.880 --> 10:29.940
Pocahontas.

10:29.940 --> 10:32.160
Meet John Smith.

10:32.160 --> 10:40.160
Captain John Smith and his men were happy to be in Chesapeake Bay.

10:40.160 --> 10:44.160
They wanted to establish a small settlement there.

10:44.160 --> 10:53.160
Captain Smith called the Big River the James River, after King James I of Britain.

10:54.160 --> 11:03.160
On May 13, 1607, he established the small settlement called Jamestown.

11:03.160 --> 11:07.160
Jamestown was on the James River.

11:07.160 --> 11:16.160
In Jamestown, the settlers built some huts, a storehouse, and a church.

11:16.160 --> 11:23.160
There were about 100 men in Jamestown in 1607.

11:23.160 --> 11:27.160
Most of them were English gentlemen.

11:27.160 --> 11:33.160
They came to the new world to find gold and riches.

11:33.160 --> 11:37.160
They did not want to be farmers.

11:37.160 --> 11:42.160
John Smith was angry with them. He said,

11:42.160 --> 11:48.160
You must all plant crops, hunt and fish. You must not be lazy.

11:48.160 --> 11:52.160
In Jamestown, there was little food.

11:52.160 --> 11:59.160
One day, Captain Smith and his men went into the forest to look for food.

11:59.160 --> 12:02.160
They walked for a long time.

12:02.160 --> 12:06.160
Then they met a big group of Indians.

12:06.160 --> 12:11.160
The Indians attacked them with their bows and arrows.

12:11.160 --> 12:15.160
They killed one of Smith's men.

12:15.160 --> 12:20.160
John Smith and his men killed two Indians.

12:20.160 --> 12:26.160
Then the Indians captured John Smith and took him away.

12:26.160 --> 12:36.160
After a long walk, John Smith stood in front of Chief Poehaten and his tribe.

12:36.160 --> 12:39.160
Everyone was silent.

12:39.160 --> 12:45.160
Pocahontas stood next to her father. She looked at John Smith.

12:45.160 --> 12:55.160
He was very tall. She looked at his red hair, his blue eyes and his white skin.

12:55.160 --> 13:00.160
He was very different from the Indian men.

13:00.160 --> 13:07.160
John Smith spoke to the Indians in sign language and a few Indian words.

13:07.160 --> 13:14.160
Great Chief, I am a friend. My men and I want to live in peace with you.

13:14.160 --> 13:20.160
Poehaten and his medicine men did not like him.

13:20.160 --> 13:27.160
John Smith gave a compass to the great chief. Poehaten looked at it.

13:27.160 --> 13:31.160
He turned it around in his hand.

13:31.160 --> 13:36.160
Why did the needle always point in the same direction?

13:36.160 --> 13:42.160
He tried to touch the needle, but a piece of ice was in front of it.

13:42.160 --> 13:47.160
The ice wasn't cold. It didn't melt.

13:47.160 --> 13:50.160
Poehaten thought it was magic.

13:50.160 --> 13:55.160
All the Indians of the tribe looked at the compass.

13:55.160 --> 13:59.160
They were surprised at the white man's magic.

13:59.160 --> 14:07.160
Pocahontas liked John Smith and his magic, but her father didn't like him.

14:07.160 --> 14:13.160
That afternoon, John Smith and his men killed two Indians.

14:13.160 --> 14:18.160
Chief Poehaten and his tribe were very angry.

14:18.160 --> 14:22.160
Now John Smith must die.

14:22.160 --> 14:27.160
Two Indian warriors pushed Captain Smith to the ground.

14:27.160 --> 14:32.160
They put his head on a very big stone.

14:32.160 --> 14:37.160
Then the Indians picked up another big stone.

14:37.160 --> 14:40.160
They wanted to kill John Smith.

14:40.160 --> 14:43.160
When Pocahontas saw this, she said,

14:43.160 --> 14:48.160
No father, please don't kill him. He isn't a bad man.

14:48.160 --> 14:55.160
Poehaten said, No, he and his men killed two Indians.

14:55.160 --> 14:57.160
He must die.

14:57.160 --> 15:02.160
The two Indians were ready to kill Captain Smith.

15:02.160 --> 15:05.160
One Indian raised his hand.

15:05.160 --> 15:06.160
No!

15:06.160 --> 15:13.160
Said Pocahontas, she jumped forward and put her head above Captain Smith's head.

15:13.160 --> 15:17.160
Please father, he must not die. Save him.

15:17.160 --> 15:23.160
Said Pocahontas, Poehaten looked at his favorite daughter.

15:23.160 --> 15:28.160
He immediately told the two Indians to stop.

15:28.160 --> 15:33.160
Everyone was surprised at Pocahontas' courage.

15:33.160 --> 15:37.160
Pocahontas saved John Smith's life.

15:37.160 --> 15:44.160
After this, Pocahontas and John Smith became great friends.

15:44.160 --> 15:51.160
John Smith taught her English and she taught him the Indian language.

15:51.160 --> 15:55.160
He gave her beautiful beads and trinkets.

15:55.160 --> 16:00.160
He told her about London and its enormous buildings.

16:00.160 --> 16:04.160
Pocahontas listened to Smith's stories.

16:04.160 --> 16:08.160
The King of England is called King James I.

16:08.160 --> 16:12.160
He lives in a beautiful palace in London.

16:12.160 --> 16:14.160
Is John Smith?

16:14.160 --> 16:16.160
Is he your chief?

16:16.160 --> 16:18.160
Asked Pocahontas.

16:18.160 --> 16:21.160
Yes, he's our leader.

16:21.160 --> 16:23.160
Said John Smith.

16:23.160 --> 16:25.160
What do the English ladies wear?

16:25.160 --> 16:28.160
Asked Pocahontas.

16:28.160 --> 16:32.160
They wear long colorful dresses, shoes and hats.

16:32.160 --> 16:34.160
They also wear jewels.

16:34.160 --> 16:37.160
Are the English ladies beautiful?

16:37.160 --> 16:41.160
Pocahontas asked, Some are beautiful and some aren't.

16:41.160 --> 16:44.160
Said John Smith.

16:44.160 --> 16:47.160
Pocahontas laughed and listened.

16:47.160 --> 16:50.160
She dreamt about London.

