18:20.160 --> 18:23.160
The Origins of Virginia.

18:24.160 --> 18:34.160
In 1606, King James I of Britain established the Virginia Company to explore the new world.

18:35.160 --> 18:41.160
It was named after Elizabeth I, the Virgin Queen.

18:41.160 --> 18:51.160
King James wanted his explorers to find gold, riches and food products in the new world.

18:51.160 --> 18:57.160
He also hoped to find a new way to go to India.

18:57.160 --> 19:04.160
Captain John Smith was one of the leaders of the Virginia Company.

19:04.160 --> 19:07.160
He was a courageous soldier.

19:07.160 --> 19:13.160
When he was young, his life was full of adventure.

19:13.160 --> 19:18.160
He and the Austrians fought against the Turks.

19:18.160 --> 19:22.160
The Austrians were very pleased with him.

19:22.160 --> 19:31.160
They gave him a horse, a scimitar, a coat of arms and the title of Captain.

19:32.160 --> 19:37.160
Then Captain Smith was captured by the Turks.

19:37.160 --> 19:42.160
He was a prisoner in Turkey, but he escaped.

19:42.160 --> 19:51.160
He crossed Russia, sailed on a pirate ship and returned to England in 1604.

19:51.160 --> 19:56.160
Captain Smith then worked for the Virginia Company.

19:56.160 --> 20:00.160
He took the English settlers to the new world.

20:00.160 --> 20:04.160
He was a strong, intelligent leader.

20:04.160 --> 20:08.160
He established the settlement of Jamestown.

20:08.160 --> 20:13.160
He explored the Chesapeake region and made maps.

20:13.160 --> 20:19.160
He made friends with many Indian tribes in the region.

20:19.160 --> 20:28.160
The settlers did not find gold and riches in the new colony, but they found the tobacco plant.

20:28.160 --> 20:35.160
In the 17th century, the tobacco plant grew only in America.

20:35.160 --> 20:40.160
The American Indians smoked the tobacco leaves.

20:40.160 --> 20:45.160
They used the leaves as medicine too.

20:45.160 --> 20:51.160
The tobacco plant became the most important product of the Virginia colony.

20:51.160 --> 20:57.160
There were many tobacco plantations along the James River.

20:57.160 --> 21:01.160
The tobacco leaves were picked and dried.

21:01.160 --> 21:06.160
Then they were sent to England and other parts of Europe.

21:06.160 --> 21:11.160
This was the beginning of an important business.

21:11.160 --> 21:15.160
Soon there were tobacco companies everywhere.

21:15.160 --> 21:23.160
With its tobacco plantations, Virginia became a very rich colony.

21:23.160 --> 21:31.160
By 1688, it produced about 10 million kilograms of tobacco.

21:31.160 --> 21:35.160
Smoking became very popular in America and Europe.

21:35.160 --> 21:42.160
It became very popular in Europe and Europe.

