22:38.160 --> 22:41.160
Chapter 3.

22:41.160 --> 22:44.160
Winter in Jamestown.

22:45.160 --> 22:50.160
The hot summer passed and the cool autumn arrived.

22:50.160 --> 22:55.160
The Jamestown settlers had little food to eat.

22:55.160 --> 22:59.160
Many settlers were ill and weak.

22:59.160 --> 23:02.160
They needed help.

23:02.160 --> 23:07.160
When winter arrived, there was no food.

23:07.160 --> 23:11.160
Pocahontas helped the Jamestown settlers.

23:12.160 --> 23:19.160
She asked her father for corn, meat, and other food.

23:19.160 --> 23:27.160
Pocahontas and other Indians brought the food to Jamestown in big baskets.

23:27.160 --> 23:34.160
The courageous Indian princess helped the settlers to live during the cold winter.

23:34.160 --> 23:38.160
Ships came to Jamestown from England.

23:38.160 --> 23:42.160
Pocahontan was not happy about this.

23:42.160 --> 23:46.160
More white men came to the new world.

23:46.160 --> 23:49.160
Pocahontan was afraid of them.

23:49.160 --> 23:53.160
He was afraid of the future.

23:53.160 --> 23:59.160
One winter day, Pocahontan sent an Indian messenger to Jamestown.

23:59.160 --> 24:03.160
He had a message for Captain Smith.

24:03.160 --> 24:07.160
My chief, Pocahontan, wants to speak to you.

24:07.160 --> 24:09.160
Follow me.

24:09.160 --> 24:15.160
John Smith followed the messenger to Pocahontan's village.

24:15.160 --> 24:18.160
Pocahontan was in his long house.

24:18.160 --> 24:22.160
John Smith sat next to him.

24:22.160 --> 24:26.160
We have no more food to give to your people.

24:26.160 --> 24:31.160
You must all leave this land now, said Pocahontan.

24:31.160 --> 24:33.160
Why must we leave?

24:33.160 --> 24:35.160
Ask John Smith.

24:35.160 --> 24:39.160
The two men talked for a long time.

24:39.160 --> 24:42.160
At midnight, Pocahontan said,

24:42.160 --> 24:44.160
It is very late.

24:44.160 --> 24:49.160
You can sleep in the small cabin near the river.

24:49.160 --> 24:52.160
Captain Smith accepted the invitation.

24:52.160 --> 24:56.160
He went to sleep in the small cabin.

24:56.160 --> 25:01.160
During the night, John Smith heard someone at the door.

25:01.160 --> 25:06.160
He got up, opened the door, and saw Pocahontas.

25:06.160 --> 25:11.160
What a surprise to see you, Pocahontas. Please come in.

25:11.160 --> 25:15.160
Captain Smith, your life is in danger.

25:15.160 --> 25:19.160
My father and the medicine men want to kill you tonight.

25:19.160 --> 25:25.160
They don't want white people to stay here. You must run away now.

25:25.160 --> 25:29.160
Dear Princess, you are saving my life again.

25:29.160 --> 25:33.160
How can I thank you? What can I give you?

25:33.160 --> 25:34.160
Asked Captain Smith,

25:34.160 --> 25:38.160
Run away now. Save yourself.

