32:59.160 --> 33:02.160
Indian life.

33:03.160 --> 33:10.160
The American Indians came from Asia about 40,000 years ago.

33:10.160 --> 33:16.160
They crossed the Bering Strait and went down to North America.

33:16.160 --> 33:20.160
These Indians were hunters.

33:20.160 --> 33:23.160
They hunted wild animals.

33:23.160 --> 33:29.160
After thousands of years, some Indians became farmers.

33:29.160 --> 33:32.160
They cultivated corn.

33:32.160 --> 33:35.160
Other Indians hunted the buffalo.

33:35.160 --> 33:41.160
They used the buffalo for food, clothing, and tepees.

33:41.160 --> 33:46.160
American Indians belonged to different tribes.

33:46.160 --> 33:49.160
Every tribe had a chief.

33:49.160 --> 33:54.160
There were hundreds of Indian tribes in America.

33:54.160 --> 33:59.160
The American Indians decorated things with beautiful colors.

33:59.160 --> 34:03.160
They made masks and decorated them.

34:03.160 --> 34:08.160
They also made pottery and statues.

34:08.160 --> 34:13.160
Indians painted pictures on big stone walls.

34:13.160 --> 34:18.160
These pictures told a story about their life.

34:18.160 --> 34:23.160
Indians were great hunters and courageous warriors.

34:23.160 --> 34:26.160
They were strong people.

34:26.160 --> 34:31.160
They loved and respected nature and animals.

34:31.160 --> 34:36.160
Different tribes lived in different kinds of homes.

34:36.160 --> 34:43.160
The wigwam, the tepee, the longhouse, and the pueblo.

34:43.160 --> 34:50.160
Indians often decorated their tepees with colorful pictures.

34:50.160 --> 34:58.160
The Indians of the Pacific coast often put big totem poles outside their longhouses.

34:58.160 --> 35:03.160
Indians used these weapons to hunt and fight.

35:03.160 --> 35:09.160
Bose and arrows, spears, knives, and tomahawks.

35:09.160 --> 35:17.160
When Captain John Smith came to the New World, some important tribes were the Apaches,

35:17.160 --> 35:25.160
the Comanches, the Hurans, the Mohicans, the Navajos, and the Sioux.

35:25.160 --> 35:30.160
At first the Indians were friendly with the white settlers.

35:30.160 --> 35:33.160
They taught the settlers how to grow crops.

35:33.160 --> 35:38.160
They also taught them how to live in the wilderness.

35:38.160 --> 35:44.160
The white settlers brought the Indians weapons and tools.

35:44.160 --> 35:49.160
Soon the settlers wanted to take the Indians' land.

35:49.160 --> 35:54.160
Many settlers came to America and they wanted land.

35:54.160 --> 35:58.160
The Indians didn't want to lose their land.

35:58.160 --> 36:01.160
The Indian wars began.

36:01.160 --> 36:04.160
Many people were killed.

36:04.160 --> 36:10.160
Finally, in the 1890s, the Indian wars ended.

36:10.160 --> 36:13.160
The Indians lost their land.

36:13.160 --> 36:18.160
America was now the land of the white settlers.

36:18.160 --> 36:24.160
Today, American Indians live on reservations.

