37:57.160 --> 38:01.160
They were very happy together.

38:01.160 --> 38:05.160
John Rolf wanted to marry Pocahontas,

38:05.160 --> 38:10.160
but Pocahontas wanted to speak to her father first.

38:10.160 --> 38:16.160
One day, Pocahontas and John Rolf went to visit Pocahontan.

38:16.160 --> 38:21.160
The great chief was pleased to see his daughter.

38:21.160 --> 38:24.160
Father, this is John Rolf.

38:24.160 --> 38:26.160
I met him in Jamestown.

38:26.160 --> 38:29.160
He is a very kind person.

38:29.160 --> 38:33.160
I love him and I'm going to marry him.

38:33.160 --> 38:37.160
You are a young woman now, Pocahontas.

38:37.160 --> 38:41.160
It is time for you to marry the man you love.

38:41.160 --> 38:45.160
Pocahontan embraced his daughter and John.

38:45.160 --> 38:47.160
Great chief.

38:47.160 --> 38:54.160
I love your daughter and I want to take care of her, said John Rolf.

38:54.160 --> 39:03.160
In April 1614, Pocahontas married John Rolf in the Anglican Church.

39:03.160 --> 39:08.160
She was the first American Indian to marry a white man.

39:08.160 --> 39:13.160
Pocahontas wore a beautiful white dress.

39:13.160 --> 39:16.160
She had flowers in her hair.

39:16.160 --> 39:22.160
She and John Rolf laughed and danced on this special day.

39:22.160 --> 39:27.160
All the people in Jamestown celebrated the marriage.

39:27.160 --> 39:32.160
There were great festivities with music and dancing.

39:32.160 --> 39:38.160
Nantakwas and many other Indians came to celebrate.

39:38.160 --> 39:43.160
At the wedding meal, there were white men and Indians.

39:43.160 --> 39:46.160
They were all good friends.

39:46.160 --> 39:50.160
They sat around a long table.

39:50.160 --> 39:54.160
They were all types of good food to eat.

39:54.160 --> 39:59.160
Pocahontas's marriage brought peace to the Virginia colony.

39:59.160 --> 40:03.160
The colony began to grow.

40:03.160 --> 40:09.160
Soon after their marriage, Pocahontas and John went to London.

40:09.160 --> 40:15.160
Pocahontas was surprised to see many new things in England.

40:15.160 --> 40:20.160
In London, she wore beautiful English clothes.

40:20.160 --> 40:23.160
Everyone wanted to meet her.

40:23.160 --> 40:27.160
She met the most important people of London.

40:27.160 --> 40:31.160
She even met King James I.

40:31.160 --> 40:35.160
Everyone loved the Indian princess.

40:35.160 --> 40:41.160
In London, Pocahontas met John Smith again after many years.

40:41.160 --> 40:44.160
This was a wonderful surprise.

40:44.160 --> 40:48.160
They talked about their adventures in Jamestown.

40:48.160 --> 40:52.160
Pocahontas and John Rolf had a son.

40:52.160 --> 40:55.160
They were very happy.

40:55.160 --> 40:58.160
They called him Thomas.

40:58.160 --> 41:04.160
After Thomas's birth, Pocahontas became very ill.

41:04.160 --> 41:11.160
She died in England in 1617, at the age of 21.

41:11.160 --> 41:14.160
This was a tragic event.

41:14.160 --> 41:17.160
Many people mourned her.

41:17.160 --> 41:21.160
They remembered the courageous Indian princess.

41:21.160 --> 41:27.160
Young Thomas was educated in Britain by his uncle, Henry Rolf.

41:27.160 --> 41:31.160
John Rolf was heartbroken.

41:31.160 --> 41:34.160
He didn't want to live in Britain.

41:34.160 --> 41:38.160
He returned to Virginia to grow tobacco.

41:38.160 --> 41:41.160
He became an important tobacco farmer.

41:41.160 --> 41:46.160
He had a very big tobacco plantation.

41:46.160 --> 41:50.160
When Thomas Rolf was an adult, he left Britain.

41:50.160 --> 41:55.160
He went to America to visit his mother's land.

41:55.160 --> 41:58.160
